			<ns0:name>halya...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/112856509894568708731/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">NaClThreadLauncher assigns user context to nacl_user array. It uses index thread_idx obtained from NaClGetThreadIdx. In 64-bit mode NaClGetThreadIdx returns increased by 1 value received from NaClThreadIdxAllocate.

NaClThreadIdxAllocate returns values from 0 to NACL_THREAD_MAX - 1. So, if a NaCl application creates NACL_THREAD_MAX threads, NaClGetThreadIdx returns NACL_THREAD_MAX and NaClThreadLauncher writes data after nacl_user array end.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2013-01-10T22:04:26.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-02-13T18:03:12.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:owner>
